title: Clemson moves to No. 3 in AP poll
text:
Clemson moves to No. 3 in AP poll Ohio State remains No. 1 amid shake-up By The Sports Xchange POSTED: 1:58 PM Oct 25 2015 UPDATED 3 mins Text Size: Tweet iStock/joecicak 
Clemson moved up three spots to No. 3 in a shake-up of the Associated Press Top 25 college football poll released Sunday. More from NBC Montana Raiders beat Chargers with air attack 
Top-ranked Ohio State (8-0) picked up 11 first-place votes following former No. 3 Utah's first loss of the season. The Buckeyes now have 39 top votes after the Buckeyes' 49-7 rout of Rutgers. 
Baylor, Clemson, LSU and TCU -- the rest of the top five -- also received first-place votes, as did seventh-ranked Alabama. 
Clemson jumped over TCU, which was off, and LSU, which beat Western Kentucky. 
Michigan State is No. 6, followed by Alabama, Stanford, Notre Dame and Iowa. 
Utah dropped 10 spots to No. 13 after losing to unranked USC. Florida State fell eight places to No. 17 after losing 22-16 to Georgia Tech on a blocked field goal that was returned for a touchdown on the game's final play. 
Florida is No. 11, followed by Oklahoma State, Utah, Oklahoma, Michigan, Memphis, Florida State, Houston, Ole Miss, Toledo, Temple, Duke, Pittsburgh and UCLA and Mississippi State.
